The amount of CO2 was determined with a Shimadzu GC 2010 (Shimadzu Corporation) equipped with a TCD detector and a HP PlotQ (30 m × 0.5 mm × 40 µm) column. The chromatograph was applied in split injection mode (rate 0.5:1). The temperature of the inlet was 200 °C. The column and the detector temperature were maintained at 90 and 150 °C, respectively. The applied carrier gas was Messer nitrogen 4.5 at 8.4 mL min−1. The samples were injected with the help of a gastight microsyringe (Hamilton). The conversion efficiency of H2 to CH4 was calculated by the modified theoretical equation [15].η=rCH4A-rCH4BrH2A-rH2D×4×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
